IPC (Inter-Process Communication) is a mechanism that allows two or more processes to exchange data and synchronize their execution. 
Since processes have separate memory spaces, they need IPC to communicate.

| IPC Mechanism      | Used For                                                |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| Pipes              | Communication between related processes (parent-child)  |
| Named Pipes (FIFO) | Communication between unrelated processes               |
| Shared Memory      | Fastest IPC, processes share a memory region            |
| Message Queues     | Exchange structured messages                            |
| Sockets            | Communication over a network or between local processes |
| Signals            | Notify a process that an event has occurred             |
